# Real Browser MCP

MCP server: `user-real-browser-mcp`. Controls the user's REAL Chrome browser - not headless. All sessions, logins, cookies are already active.

## Rules

- NEVER close tabs you didn't create
- NEVER navigate away from pages the user is working on without asking
- Prefer `browser_snapshot` over `browser_screenshot` (cheaper, faster, parseable)
- Snapshots return refs that break after navigation/scroll/DOM changes - always re-snapshot before using refs
- Use `browser_evaluate` for anything the other tools can't do (dropdowns, modals, complex DOM)

## Tools

### Navigation & Tabs
- `browser_navigate` - Go to URL. Params: `url`, `waitUntil`
- `browser_tabs` - List/create/close/focus tabs. Params: `action` (list|create|close|focus), `tabId`, `url`

### Interaction
- `browser_click` - Click element. Params: `ref` OR `selector` (CSS), `button` (left|right|middle), `doubleClick`
- `browser_type` - Type text. Params: `ref` OR `selector`, `text`, `clear`
- `browser_press_key` - Keyboard. Params: `key`, `modifiers` (ctrl|alt|shift|meta), `ref`, `selector`
- `browser_scroll` - Scroll. Params: `direction`, `amount`, `selector`, `toElement`, `position` (top|bottom)
- `browser_hover` - Hover element. Params: `ref` OR `selector`
- `browser_select` - Select from `<select>`. Params: `ref` OR `selector`, `value` OR `label` OR `index`

### Reading
- `browser_snapshot` - Accessibility tree with refs. Params: `selector`, `compact` (default true - interactive only, ~70% smaller)
- `browser_screenshot` - Capture visible tab as image. Params: `format` (png|jpeg), `quality`
- `browser_text` - Get page text content. Params: `selector`, `maxLength`
- `browser_find` - Find elements by natural language. Params: `query`, `limit`

### JavaScript & Dialogs
- `browser_evaluate` - Execute JS in page context, return result. Params: `expression` (supports async/await)
- `browser_handle_dialog` - Handle alert/confirm/prompt. Call BEFORE triggering actions that may cause dialogs. Params: `action` (accept|dismiss), `promptText`

### Waiting
- `browser_wait` - Wait for element or delay. Params: `selector`, `state` (visible|hidden|attached), `timeout`, `delay`

### Debug
- `browser_console` - Read console messages (read-only). Params: `clear`
- `browser_network` - Read network requests. Params: `filter` (regex), `clear`

## Workflow

1. `browser_snapshot` to see page structure and get element refs
2. Use refs (e.g. "e12") with `browser_click`, `browser_type`, etc.
3. For complex UI (React dropdowns, portals, overlays) - use `browser_evaluate` with JS
4. After actions, snapshot again to verify result
5. `browser_wait` before interacting with dynamically loaded content

## React/SPA Tips

- Custom dropdowns: use `browser_evaluate` to click options that don't appear in the accessibility tree
- Virtual scroll containers: `browser_scroll` with `selector` targeting the scroll container
- After scroll, re-snapshot - refs are invalidated
- `browser_press_key` for keyboard shortcuts (Enter to submit, Escape to close modals)
- `browser_handle_dialog` before actions that might trigger alert/confirm/prompt
